[The Argentinians are to be truly congratulated on this very significant reduction in anthrax incidence. Yes, they had an outbreak in Rauch in 2017 and had one earlier this year (2018) in the municipality of Paraje Muñoz, Laprida county, in a herd that had not been vaccinated in spite of the compulsory livestock vaccination in place in Buenos Aires province. Welcome to the reality of anthrax eradication. Until the estancia owners realise that procrastination is not the answer we will see the occasional outbreak until universal vaccination is in place, when the disease will be silent. But the good news is that we are in sight of seeing livestock anthrax being eradicated from the province of Buenos Aires and hopefully the other provinces will take note of this major achievement of a very serious reduction. - Mod.MHJ

Maps of Argentina: http://www.argentina.org.au/images/mapa-politico-argentina.jpg and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5766784,53505]
